<p>Given a video file (e.g. test.mkv), is it possible to output the data points used to create a waveform using ffmpeg (or any other tool)? </p>  <p>I'm looking to create a file that maps audio level to time, so that I can parse the data. Most of the examples I am finding, output an image. </p>  <p>The closest I've gotten is generating raw binary data with: <code>ffmpeg -i test.mkv -ac 1 -filter:a aresample=8000 -map 0:a -c:a pcm_s16le -f data -</code></p>